parts.text:
Show me how a specific form component should handle validation errors from the backend. Take the example of an event creation form.

When the user submits the form and the backend returns a VALIDATION_ERROR with field-level details like this:

{
  "error": {
	"code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
	"message": "Invalid event data",
	"details": [
  	{ "field": "title", "issue": "Title is required" },
  	{ "field": "start_time", "issue": "Must be a future date" },
  	{ "field": "end_time", "issue": "Must be after start time" }
	],
	"traceId": "abc123"
  }
}

The component should:
1. Parse the details array from the error response.
2. Map each detail to the corresponding form field and display the error message inline, next to the field.
3. Also handle the case where there are no field-level details (just a general validation message) — show it as a form-level error above the submit button.
4. Clear previous server-side errors when the user starts editing a field.

Show the pattern conceptually — the key logic for mapping backend error details to frontend form fields. Keep it generalizable so I can apply this pattern to any form in my app.

