```

Notes / best practices
- Use a consistent field naming convention between backend `details[].field` and form control names (or provide a map if they differ).
- Use `control.errors.server` (or another unique key) so Angular validators still work and you can clear only server errors.
- Always clear server-side errors on `valueChanges` to avoid stale messages.
- If using template-driven forms, adapt by holding an errors map and toggling messages on control input events.
- Keep the interceptor behavior: it must re-throw `VALIDATION_ERROR` so components can access `HttpErrorResponse.error.details`.

This pattern generalizes: any form can call `applyBackendValidation(form, details)` after catching a `VALIDATION_ERROR` and show a form-level message if the helper returns one.

